\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. C. turcicum} Janka, {\i Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  23}: 242 (1873). Corm up to 3 × 2 cm, ovoid; tunic dark brown, coriaceous, with a long neck. Leaves 5-9, up to 15 cm × 6-25 mm, developing after anthesis, linear-lanceolate, obtuse to subacute, glaucous margins somewhat undulate, ciliate (sometimes obscurely so). Flowers 3-8; perianth-segments 30-40 × 4-13 mm, deep crimson-purple, occasionally paler, oblong to linear-elliptical, obtuse to subacute. Filaments up to 15 mm; anthers 4-7 mm, yellow (occasionally purplish); pollen yellow. Styles straight, slightly curved at apex; stigmas long-decurrent. Capsule 20-30 mm oblong. Flowering August to October.{\i  Meadows. E. part of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju Tu.
\par

