\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. C. callicymbium} Stearn & Stefanov,{\i  Jour. Bot}. ({\i London}){\b  72}: 343 (1934). Corm 3-4 × 3-3·5 cm, subglobose; tunic dark brown, subeoriaceous, with a long neck. Leaves 3-5, 25-40 cm × 10-50 mm, developing after anthesis, linear or narrowly linear. Flowers 2-4; perianth-segments up to 35 × 8-13 mm, purplish-lilac, slightly darker at base, oblanceolate to narrowly elliptical, obtuse. Filaments up to 12 mm; anthers 4·5-6 mm, black; pollen yellow. Styles straight, curved at the apex; stigmas long decurrent. Capsule 20-30 mm, narrowly ovoid. Flowering September. •{\i  S.W. Bulgaria.} Bu ?Gr.
